Package: formalCoverage
Title: Tests Functions Source Code for Unused Arguments
Version: 0.0.2
Authors@R: person("Hugh", "Parsonage", email = "hugh.parsonage@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Determines whether any arguments in a function have obviously not been used. Useful to avoid bugs that may otherwise evade diagnostic tools such as unit testing and code coverage.
